SECTION 1
PROJECT OVERVIEW

1.1  Objective
This project builds an end-to-end, production-grade Resume Parser that accepts PDF and DOCX files and returns a fully structured JSON object containing all relevant candidate information — without relying on any third-party parsing APIs, OpenAI APIs, or paid LLM services. Every component is open-source, self-hosted, and owned entirely by your engineering team.
The parser must handle real-world resume diversity: graphic-heavy layouts, multi-column PDFs, inconsistent date formats, non-Western names, varied section naming conventions, and abbreviated job titles. It must process resumes programmatically at scale without human intervention per document.
1.2  Accuracy Target
The accuracy target is 85–90% field-level F1 score across all entity types on a held-out test set of at least 150 diverse resumes. This is not a vanity metric — it means that 85–90 out of every 100 entity extractions are correct.
